incompetence 2023-01-18 12:37 AM
See I generally don’t know other people’s level of knowledge, and assume they’re at a baseline. Let’s say that’s a baseline 15 points in a 100-point scale. Maybe some of their 15 points are on purple portions of the subject, while my 30 or 40 points are not range or red or green. No matter how much I know about something, it is extremely rare for someone e to not share new information or cover a topic I’ve rarely heard about. Like, I might know 40 points about the red and orange aspects of something, but when I’m discussing it with someone else we mutually gain from each others’ “points”- I get purple points, and share my orange and red ones. However, some people assume that they know everything and have nothing to learn from others, and thus when they explain things it comes across as extremely condescending and/or rude. (Help me out if I ever become one of those people please lol)
